# game/lorem1.rpy:151
translate Korean lorem1_e802b109:

    # Lo normal "I can assure you I am a fully grown adult. My species doesn't get much bigger than this."
    Lo normal "저 성인 맞아요. 제 종족은 이거보다 크게 자라진 않거든요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:153
translate Korean lorem1_649fddf0:

    # Lo happy "Speaking of which, are you fully grown yet? How big do humans usually get and how do you stack up, comparatively speaking?"
    Lo happy "말이 나와서 그러는데요, 대사님은 성인이신가요? 인간들은 보통 얼마나 커지나요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:155
translate Korean lorem1_dd38c1dc:

    # Lo think "Oh, and would you mind if I took some notes?"
    Lo think "아, 노트라도 가지고 왔어야 했나?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:157
translate Korean lorem1_45499fc8:

    # c "Before we get to that, you haven't even told me yet what exactly all this is for. Are you sure you're not a reporter?"
    c "일단 그 질문에 답해드리기 전에, 뭐 때문인지도 말씀해주시지 않았잖아요. 기자가 아니라고 하셨죠?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:159
translate Korean lorem1_260d481d:

    # Lo happy "If I was, Sebastian wouldn’t have let me meet you in the first place."
    Lo happy "제가 기자였다면, 세바스찬이 처음에 당신을 만나지 못하게 했을 걸요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:161
translate Korean lorem1_57ab5828:

    # c "And I thought the uniform was just a clever disguise."
    c "그 유니폼은 위장용인줄로만 알았는데요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:163
translate Korean lorem1_a750447a:

    # Lo normal "It's real, though. Sebastian knows I work for the local post office."
    Lo normal "그건 진짜에요. 세바스찬도 제가 지역 우체부로 일하는 건 알아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:165
translate Korean lorem1_c4112abb:

    # c "Excuse me, but this still doesn't really tell me anything about why I'm here. You're a postman who wants to interview me for... what, exactly?"
    c "잠깐만요, 그래도 제가 왜 여깄어야하는지 설명이 되는 것 같진 않은데요. 당신은 우체부고, 저를 인터뷰하길 원하는데... 뭘 위해서에요, 정확히?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:167
translate Korean lorem1_4c2ac08e:

    # Lo relieved "Sorry, I guess I got ahead of myself here. Maybe a full introduction is in order, and after that, you can still decide whether you want to go through with this or not."
    Lo relieved "죄송해요, 제가 너무 앞섰나봐요. 그러면 먼저 처음부터 설명을 드려야겠네요, 그러면 이 일을 계속 밀고나가실 건지 아니면 그만두실 건지 결정하실 수 있겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:186
translate Korean lorem1_6a88e8e8:

    # Lo happy "I recently graduated college with a degree in computing and moved in here with a good friend of mine."
    Lo happy "저는 최근에 컴퓨터를 전공해 대학을 졸업하고 친구와 함께 이사를 왔어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:188
translate Korean lorem1_98593d8f:

    # Lo think "This town doesn't exactly offer the best opportunities to put my degree to good use, though."
    Lo think "하지만 이 지역에선 제 전공을 활용할 기회가 딱히 없을 것 같아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:190
translate Korean lorem1_f52dcfe5:

    # c "Then why move here in the first place?"
    c "그러면 왜 여기로 이사온거에요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:192
translate Korean lorem1_d8bc587f:

    # Lo normal "Living in the city can be very expensive. I can always move later when I get a job there. I've got other plans right now, though."
    Lo normal "도시에서 살려면 돈이 필요해서요. 도시에서 직업을 얻을 때 언제든지 이사갈 수 있잖아요. 지금은 다른 계획이 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:194
translate Korean lorem1_3ad10c5b:

    # Lo happy "I'm working on a video game."
    Lo happy "비디오 게임을 개발하고 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:203
translate Korean lorem1_b78abb33:

    # Lo normal "You got it!"
    Lo normal "맞아요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:209
translate Korean lorem1_2e662216:

    # Lo relieved "But this is serious!"
    Lo relieved "하지만 이건 심각하다고요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:217
translate Korean lorem1_1db2bc1a:

    # Lo "Exactly!"
    Lo "정확하시네요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:225
translate Korean lorem1_2d0c2152:

    # Lo "Video games and computers are just starting to catch on in places like this town. Making good content will be very important to give a good first impression."
    Lo "비디오 게임과 컴퓨터는 이제 막 이 지역에 자리잡으려고 하고 있어요. 좋은 컨텐츠를 만드는 게 좋은 첫 인상을 만드는 데 아주 중요하죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:227
translate Korean lorem1_b7b18181:

    # Lo happy "And humans have always been part of our media - books, movies, and now games. With you on our side, this could be an amazing opportunity!"
    Lo happy "그리고 이런 매체들에 인간은 항상 빠지지 않았죠. 책이건, 영화건, 이제는 게임까지요. 당신이 저희를 도와주신다면, 이건 큰 기회에요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:229
translate Korean lorem1_ed1e847f:

    # c "Well..."
    c "음..."

# game/lorem1.rpy:231
translate Korean lorem1_60287eb6:

    # Lo shy "Oh. Maybe this wasn't such a good idea after all."
    Lo shy "아. 물론 이게 좋은 아이디어는 아닐 수도 있겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:239
translate Korean lorem1_e08aa85e:

    # Lo relieved "I don't know. You don't seem so thrilled about doing this anymore..."
    Lo relieved "저도 모르겠어요. 대사님은 더 이상 이 일을 하고 싶지 않으시겠죠..."

# game/lorem1.rpy:249
translate Korean lorem1_8daf20aa:

    # Lo "Besides, your job must be really stressful, and you're probably already in the spotlight all the time. And now, to top it all off, you get some postman harassing you for an interview."
    Lo "게다가, 대사님도 꽤나 피곤하시겠어요. 항상 주목을 받고 계실테니까요. 근데 거기에, 모든 걸 제쳐두고 웬 우체부 하나가 당신에게 인터뷰를 해달라며 괴롭히고 있으니..."

# game/lorem1.rpy:251
translate Korean lorem1_2660554d:

    # Lo "If you wanted to leave, I'd get that."
    Lo "지금 가셔도, 전 이해할 수 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:257
translate Korean lorem1_dce6f68c:

    # c "Well, I'm already here and have nothing else to do, so let's make the most of this."
    c "음, 전 이미 와버렸고, 따로 할 것도 없으니, 이 시간을 최대한 활용해야하지 않겠어요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:259
translate Korean lorem1_55eb3920:

    # Lo happy "Yes! Thank you!"
    Lo happy "오예! 고마워요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:265
translate Korean lorem1_aded8efe:

    # c "Well, this was a waste of time."
    c "뭐, 결국 시간낭비에 불과했네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:267
translate Korean lorem1_87c9bd59:

    # Lo shy "Sorry. I won't bother you again."
    Lo shy "죄송해요. 다신 귀찮게 하지 않을게요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:269
translate Korean lorem1_21ec9701:

    # c "I hope so."
    c "그랬으면 좋겠군요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:271
translate Korean lorem1_6e20b877:

    # m "Without another word, I got up from our table and left."
    m "이외에 다른 말은 없이, 나는 일어나 술집을 떠났다."

# game/lorem1.rpy:299
translate Korean lorem1_1b74c6ae:

    # c "At least I won't have to be so careful now. With a reporter, I'd have to worry about things being misinterpreted or being taken out of context."
    c "적어도 지금만큼은 제가 조심해야할 필요는 없으니까요. 당신이 기자였다면, 잘못 해석될 수 있는 말이나 주제에서 벗어나는 말을 삼가야 하잖아요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:301
translate Korean lorem1_8062b0e2:

    # Lo normal "You should still be careful. What you tell me now will influence how your entire species will be represented in my game."
    Lo normal "그래도 조심하셔야해요. 지금부터 말씀해주시는 건 제 게임에서 표현되는 인간들의 모습에 영향을 끼칠테니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:303
translate Korean lorem1_5fef0849:

    # Lo happy "Don't worry, though. I'll treat this delicate matter with the required finesse."
    Lo happy "하지만 걱정하지 마세요. 그런 미묘한 문제 쯤은 제가 적절히 처리할테니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:322
translate Korean lorem1_fc346745:

    # Lo think "How should we do this? Let me think..."
    Lo think "그럼 뭐부터 시작할까요? 잠시만요..."

# game/lorem1.rpy:324
translate Korean lorem1_7e729438:

    # c "Why do you want to make this game in the first place?"
    c "애초에 왜 게임을 만드려고 하는 건가요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:326
translate Korean lorem1_3097ad9e:

    # Lo happy "I've always wanted to make a video game. I've had this idea for a while, and it seems now is the right time to do it. It's almost as if you arrived at the perfect moment."
    Lo happy "전 항상 비디오 게임을 만들고 싶었어요. 한동안은 마음속으로만 생각했었는데 지금이 딱 적기인 것 같아요. 대사님이 완벽하게 적절히 온 것 같지 않아요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:328
translate Korean lorem1_51a478e0:

    # c "I don't know. Don't you think my visit will overshadow your efforts? People may not be so interested in playing a game about humans anymore if they had a real one show up."
    c "잘 모르겠네요. 제 방문이 당신의 노력을 덮어버리진 않을까요? 인간들의 실체를 알게된다면 사람들은 더 이상 게임에 흥미를 가지고 하려고 하지 않을 텐데요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:330
translate Korean lorem1_390e2221:

    # Lo normal "Good point, but the vast majority won't get to meet you personally, anyway. If I say I did and modeled the humans in the game after you, people will flock to it to get a similar experience."
    Lo normal "맞아요, 하지만 어쨌거나 대부분은 당신을 개인적으로 만나지 못했으니까요. 제가 직접 만나봐서 게임 속 인간들의 모델을 당신으로 삼았다고 하면, 사람들은 간접 경험을 위해 몰려들테죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:338
translate Korean lorem1_adcb0d58:

    # Lo think "I guess you could say so."
    Lo think "말씀하신 게 맞는 것 같네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:344
translate Korean lorem1_349dd55e:

    # Lo relieved "That's just a necessary evil, I think. They have to know somehow."
    Lo relieved "그 정도는 필요악이라고 생각해요. 어쨌든 사람들도 알아야하니까..."

# game/lorem1.rpy:352
translate Korean lorem1_140ef85b:

    # Lo happy "Awesome!"
    Lo happy "굉장하네요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:359
translate Korean lorem1_2b1c8f4f:

    # c "Okay, but why focus on humans? What makes us so important?"
    c "하지만 왜 인간들에 초점을 두는 거에요? 뭐가 우리를 중요하게 만드는 건데요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:361
translate Korean lorem1_e5ba7d6f:

    # Lo think "If there’s one thing that people here love, it’s humans. It doesn’t matter if they just see them in the media or believe in them as mythical creatures."
    Lo think "이 곳 사람들이 사랑하는 것이 딱 하나 있다면, 그건 인간이에요. 언론에서나 보이는 존재로 보든지, 신화적인 존재로 믿든지 그건 중요하지 않아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:363
translate Korean lorem1_1526dff6:

    # Lo normal "For me, humans were always real. I just didn't know whether I'd ever get a chance to meet one myself. I guess I can cross that one off the bucket list."
    Lo normal "전 인간이 실존할 거라 믿었어요. 다만 제가 인간들을 만날 수 있을 기회가 있을 지 알 수 없었을 뿐이죠. 음, 이제 버킷 리스트에서 하나를 지워버릴 수 있겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:365
translate Korean lorem1_242918ac:

    # Lo happy "Now that we're here, I can tell you that no expense will be spared to make our portrayal of humans as accurate as possible."
    Lo happy "아무튼 우리가 여기 모였으니, 인간을 정확하게 묘사하기 위해서라면 어떤 것이라도 감수할 수 있을 것이라 장담해드릴 수 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:383
translate Korean lorem1_86be8d24:

    # Lo normal "For good reason! I just love humans."
    Lo normal "좋은 이유로요! 전 그저 인간들이 좋을 뿐인걸요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:385
translate Korean lorem1_3ee17091:

    # c "If you say it like that, it actually ends up sounding pretty weird."
    c "그렇게 말씀하시니까, 사실 저한텐 좀 이상하게 들리네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:387
translate Korean lorem1_1c08cd7f:

    # c "Besides, what if I turn out to be a horrible person? What would you think about humans then?"
    c "게다가, 제가 못된 사람으로 밝혀지면 어쩌시게요? 그러면 당신은 인간에 대해 어떻게 생각하실 건가요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:389
translate Korean lorem1_9bf80b9c:

    # Lo think "It wouldn't change anything, because I wouldn't base my opinion of an entire species on interactions with a single individual."
    Lo think "별로 생각이 달라지진 않을 거에요, 저도 모두를 일부만 보고 단정짓고 싶지는 않으니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:391
translate Korean lorem1_054e3918:

    # c "Then what is your current opinion of us based on?"
    c "그럼 우리에 대해서 어떤 기준으로 판단하시는데요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:393
translate Korean lorem1_9420a168:

    # Lo normal "Just the myths we have and the previous portrayals of humans in our media, but I suppose that's why I'm here talking with you right now. I want the truth, and all of it!"
    Lo normal "그냥 우리 세계에서 전해지는 신화들과 여러 매체에서 보여지는 인간들에 대한 과거 묘사들이죠. 하지만 제가 여기서 대사님과 대화를 나누고 있는 이유는, 그에 대한 진실 뿐만 아니라 모든 걸 알기 위해 온 것이죠!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:395
translate Korean lorem1_15f9c1a5:

    # c "Telling you all of it might not be such a good idea..."
    c "지금 모든 걸 다 말씀드리는 건 별로 좋은 생각이 아닐 수도 있어요..."

# game/lorem1.rpy:397
translate Korean lorem1_ef14dde8:

    # Lo think "Oh yeah, I guess that would take a lot more time than we have today."
    Lo think "아, 맞아요, 이보다 훨씬 더 많은 시간이 걸릴 것 같네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:399
translate Korean lorem1_620bc3d3:

    # c "Anyway, what's the actual game about? What do you do?"
    c "아무튼, 뭐에 대한 게임인가요? 무슨 일을 하시고요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:401
translate Korean lorem1_579745a7:

    # Lo happy "It's a community simulation game. It all starts with the player character moving into a procedurally generated community, which is inhabited by all kinds of mythical creatures. Humans included."
    Lo happy "사회 시뮬레이션 게임이에요. 플레이어의 캐릭터가 절차적으로 만들어진 지역으로 이사하는 것부터 시작해요. 사회엔 여러 신화에 나오는 생명들이 있죠. 그 중에 인간도 있고요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:403
translate Korean lorem1_fb9591f5:

    # c "Mythical creatures like humans. Mmm-hmmm."
    c "인간처럼 신화적인 생명체라. 으-흠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:405
translate Korean lorem1_b404187b:

    # Lo "Not only are the towns you move into unique, but the inhabitants are, too. There are a variety of traits that get randomized, both in looks and personality."
    Lo "이사하게 되는 지역은 독특하죠. 지역 뿐만 아니라, 주민들도요. 외모와 성격 모두가 무작위로 변하는 다양성이 있을 거에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:407
translate Korean lorem1_d879a92b:

    # Lo "There are many things you can do, but it's very open-ended and you can live your life there however you want to."
    Lo "자유도가 높아 할 수 있는 일이 많아서, 말 그대로 원하는 대로 그 곳에서 살 수 있는 거에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:415
translate Korean lorem1_fafe2bd6:

    # Lo relieved "Well, I guess you're not part of the target audience, then."
    Lo relieved "음, 그러면 대사님이 주 고객층은 아니겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:423
translate Korean lorem1_491774d2:

    # Lo normal "It is! At least, I hope others feel the same way about it."
    Lo normal "그렇죠! 적어도, 다른 사람들도 그렇게 생각하면 좋겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:429
translate Korean lorem1_c4bbdf67:

    # Lo think "Oh, really?"
    Lo think "오, 그래요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:431
translate Korean lorem1_343057fe:

    # Lo happy "I couldn't ask for a better compliment than that!"
    Lo happy "그것보다 더 좋은 평가는 없을 것 같네요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:436
translate Korean lorem1_40ad1523:

    # c "What other mythical creatures are there besides humans?"
    c "인간들 말고도 다른 신화적인 생명체는 뭐가 있어요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:438
translate Korean lorem1_fca12b73:

    # Lo think "I haven’t worked that out yet, but humans alone give us a lot of material to work with."
    Lo think "그건 아직 생각해두지 않았지만, 인간만으로도 충분한 자료를 수집할 수 있을 것 같아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:440
translate Korean lorem1_be8b7287:

    # c "How so?"
    c "어떻게요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:442
translate Korean lorem1_b613766c:

    # Lo normal "The question of the mythical human can be tackled in a variety of ways. There are many different interpretations of what humans are like."
    Lo normal "신화적인 인간에 대한 문제는 여러 방법으로 설명될 수 있죠. 인간이 어떻게 생겼는 지 여러 해석들이 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:444
translate Korean lorem1_56a7507d:

    # c "For example?"
    c "예를 들자면요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:446
translate Korean lorem1_2ad9e663:

    # Lo happy "In general, the mythical human can be divided into three categories: Firstly, the human as a physical creature; secondly, the human as a non-physical entity; and thirdly, the human as a spiritual being."
    Lo happy "일반적으로, 신화 속 인간에 대한 묘사는 세 가지로 나뉘죠. 첫 번째로, 인간은 실체가 있는 생명체다. 두 번째, 인간은 실체가 없는 개체다. 마지막으로, 인간은 영적인 존재다."

# game/lorem1.rpy:448
translate Korean lorem1_4facd386:

    # c "Let's start with the physical aspects."
    c "그럼 실체가 있는 생명체라는 쪽부터 시작해보죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:450
translate Korean lorem1_12a75e24:

    # Lo normal "Sure. Since one of our myths tells us that the human who created us eventually turned into a dragon, there is a lot of room for interpretation as to how similar humans actually are to dragons."
    Lo normal "좋아요. 한 신화에선 우리를 창조한 인간이 용으로 변했다고 해요. 이 신화에 따르면 인간이 용과 얼마나 유사한 지 여러 방면으로 해석이 가능하겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:452
translate Korean lorem1_c28061a0:

    # Lo think "I can see you don't have wings, but most of us are able to create fire in some way, or at least have a breath weapon. How about you?"
    Lo think "날개가 없다는 건 확실히 봐서 알겠지만, 우리 용족들은 어떤 식으로든 불을 만들어내거나, 적어도 브레스같은 걸 뿜어낼 수 있죠. 대사님은요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:459
translate Korean lorem1_d275ced1:

    # Lo "I don't think that counts."
    Lo "그건 아니겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:465
translate Korean lorem1_4e5846ff:

    # Lo normal "Not really. Having hands that are dextrous enough to do that is remarkable, though."
    Lo normal "그건 아니지만, 그 정도로 섬세한 손을 가지고 있다는 건 새겨들을만 하네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:475
translate Korean lorem1_a6d6377a:

    # Lo happy "Really? That's amazing!"
    Lo happy "정말요? 놀라운데요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:477
translate Korean lorem1_cf49fd2e:

    # c "I was just kidding."
    c "농담이에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:479
translate Korean lorem1_8130a854:

    # Lo relieved "You shouldn't joke about things like that. This is serious."
    Lo relieved "그런 농담은 하지마세요. 이건 진지하다고요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:481
translate Korean lorem1_86148265:

    # c "Alright."
    c "알았어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:488
translate Korean lorem1_b35e3b39:

    # Lo "It is a bit strange, though, because our myths also say that you gave that ability to us."
    Lo "그건 좀 이상하네요. 우리 신화에선 당신들이 우리에게 그런 능력을 줬다고 하거든요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:490
translate Korean lorem1_c5aed8d5:

    # c "Interesting."
    c "재밌네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:492
translate Korean lorem1_0cef7eef:

    # Lo happy "Maybe it’s meant to be taken literally – meaning that when that ability was given to us, you lost it."
    Lo happy "아마 그건 말 그대로 우리에게 나눠주고 잃어버렸다는 것이겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:494
translate Korean lorem1_8054cb2a:

    # c "Or maybe we never had it in the first place."
    c "어쩌면 우린 처음부터 그런 능력은 없었을 수도 있겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:496
translate Korean lorem1_efda574e:

    # c "Humans are known to have created a lot of things out of nothing. After all, we only needed to discover how to create and use fire, because we didn't have a natural ability to do so."
    c "인간들은 무에서 유를 창조하는 것으로 알려져있죠. 물론, 선천적인 능력은 없어서 불을 만들고 이용하는 방법을 발견해야했지만요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:498
translate Korean lorem1_177d8150:

    # c "We have a proverb that sums this up pretty well."
    c "아마 이 속담 하나로 요약할 수 있겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:500
translate Korean lorem1_0bfb9c67:

    # Lo normal "What is it?"
    Lo normal "무슨 속담이요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:502
translate Korean lorem1_4a5b7618:

    # c "Necessity is the mother of invention."
    c "필요는 발명의 어머니다."

# game/lorem1.rpy:504
translate Korean lorem1_c3d29a7c:

    # Lo think "So a lack of natural abilities drove innovation forward. What an interesting thought."
    Lo think "선천적인 능력이 없다는 것이 오히려 더 나아갈 수 있도록 만들었군요. 흥미로운 생각이에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:506
translate Korean lorem1_acf8adb4:

    # c "Here's another thing: You may have many different images of humans, but in the end, only one can be right."
    c "하나 더, 인간에 대해 여러 속설들이 있겠지만, 결국 맞는 건 하나 일 수 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:508
translate Korean lorem1_6cfa7aeb:

    # c "It's also possible that what you've been led to believe about humans doesn't actually refer to us at all."
    c "게다가 인간에 대한 설이 실제 모습과는 다를 수도 있죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:510
translate Korean lorem1_65122c50:

    # Lo relieved "Are you implying that you aren't human?"
    Lo relieved "그건 대사님이 인간이 아닐 수도 있다는 뜻인가요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:512
translate Korean lorem1_b7f880a3:

    # c "No, I'm just saying that if you really had been in contact with humans before as your myths imply, they would need to belong to the same species as me, and thus be very similar to myself."
    c "아뇨, 당신 말처럼 실제로 용족들이 인간들과 만났었다면, 그 인간들은 우리와 같은 종일 것이고, 실제로 저와 유사하겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:514
translate Korean lorem1_5c00227f:

    # c "If they aren't, then either they weren't humans at all, or have very different origins."
    c "반대로 만나지 않았었더라면, 그들은 인간이 아닐 것이에요. 아니면 다른 종일 수도 있겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:516
translate Korean lorem1_96de6db3:

    # Lo think "So you say there is a possibility that our humans and your humans may be something different altogether?"
    Lo think "그러면 대사님같은 인간이 우리가 알고있는 인간과 뭔가 다를 수도 있다는 건가요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:518
translate Korean lorem1_637351f1:

    # Lo happy "I suppose you are right in the way that our images of humans are very inconsistent. They certainly can't all be humans in the way that we would refer to a single species. The name should probably be reserved for yours."
    Lo happy "하긴 우리가 생각하는 인간들의 모습에 일관성이 없으니, 대사님이 맞는 것 같아요. 단 하나의 종만 가지고 그걸 인간이라고 단정지을 순 없는 법이죠. 이름은 우리가 정하는 게 아니라 대사님이 정하시는 게 맞겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:520
translate Korean lorem1_72d32989:

    # Lo normal "And we haven't even touched on the other two categories of humans."
    Lo normal "게다가 우린 다른 두 종류의 인간과도 만나보지 못했는걸요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:522
translate Korean lorem1_9190026a:

    # c "What did you call them again?"
    c "그 두 종류가 뭐라고 하셨죠?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:524
translate Korean lorem1_e48d651f:

    # Lo happy "Non-physical human entities and spiritual humans."
    Lo happy "실체가 없는 개체와 영적인 존재요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:526
translate Korean lorem1_7f1295b3:

    # c "What's the difference?"
    c "차이가 뭐죠?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:528
translate Korean lorem1_6bb06f89:

    # Lo think "Honestly, the definitions get a bit muddled here. Going by conventional belief, a ghost could be a human who has died and thus changed into a different form. We would call this a spiritual human."
    Lo think "솔직히, 정의가 살짝 헷갈리긴 해요. 전통적으로 내려오는 믿음에 따르면요, 인간은 죽으면 다른 형태로 변해 귀신이 되는데, 우리는 이를 영적인 인간이라 하죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:530
translate Korean lorem1_5b7b2cac:

    # Lo normal "An angel, on the other hand, would be classified as a non-physical entity."
    Lo normal "그와는 별개로 천사 쪽은 실체가 없는 개체로 분류되고요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:532
translate Korean lorem1_e3d49b89:

    # c "What do you know about angels?"
    c "천사에 대해 어떤 걸 아세요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:534
translate Korean lorem1_19a36f81:

    # Lo happy "Angels basically look like humans with wings. Their existence in ancient scripts was used to lend some credence to the theories about humans having become dragons."
    Lo happy "천사는 인간들과 똑같이 생겼지만 날개가 있죠. 그게 인간이 용으로 변했다는 이론에 어느 정도 신빙성을 더해주죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:536
translate Korean lorem1_cafbb74d:

    # c "Because of the wings?"
    c "날개때문에요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:538
translate Korean lorem1_93b4c2a4:

    # Lo "Exactly."
    Lo "정확해요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:540
translate Korean lorem1_f66ed97f:

    # c "But some of your dragon species don't have wings, either."
    c "하지만 용족들 중에서도 날개가 없는 용도 있잖아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:542
translate Korean lorem1_e2063eb2:

    # Lo think "Yes. As I said, once you start delving into that kind of stuff, it all becomes very convoluted."
    Lo think "맞아요. 제가 말씀드렸듯이, 그렇게 세세하고 파고 들어가기 시작하면, 모든 게 복잡해질거에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:544
translate Korean lorem1_b57cf12b:

    # c "When we met, you also told me something about a four-headed human."
    c "우리가 처음 만났을 때도 머리가 4개 달린 인간에 대해서 말해줬잖아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:546
translate Korean lorem1_cd5dac38:

    # Lo normal "Right. With that we'd go into the realm of creatures that just don't make much sense at all."
    Lo normal "맞아요. 만약 그 설이 맞다면 이야기가 말도 안되는 생물들의 영역까지 가겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:548
translate Korean lorem1_62c174e9:

    # Lo think "Having four heads just seems unlikely from an evolutionary perspective."
    Lo think "진화의 측면에서 봤을 때 머리 4개는 좀 말이 안되니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:550
translate Korean lorem1_5be894cd:

    # Lo "That might not really matter if we were talking about a non-physical entity or a spiritual being, though."
    Lo "근데 사실 실체가 없다는 둥 영적인 존재라는 둥 이런 얘기를 하고 있으니 별 문제는 되진 않겠지만요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:552
translate Korean lorem1_142a8591:

    # c "So in the end, you have a lot of different ideas whose only connection to each other is that you use the word human to describe them in some way."
    c "결론만 말하자면, 사람들은 인간에 대한 여러 생각들을 가지고 있지만, 결국 그 생각들은 모두 인간이라는 존재를 어떻게든 묘사하고 있다는 거에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:554
translate Korean lorem1_a133a251:

    # Lo normal "And they share at least some basic characteristics. You fit those as well, by the way."
    Lo normal "그리고 적어도 몇몇 특징들은 같죠. 그리고 대사님께서 그 특징들을 가지고 있고요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:556
translate Korean lorem1_66b483cd:

    # c "What are they?"
    c "그 특징이 뭔데요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:558
translate Korean lorem1_223625a4:

    # Lo think "You certainly are not a reptile like us, but you don't look like a conventional mammal either."
    Lo think "대사님이 우리처럼 파충류는 아니지만, 일반적인 포유류처럼 보이진 않잖아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:560
translate Korean lorem1_d21ff05e:

    # c "We are mammals, though."
    c "음, 우린 포유류가 맞아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:562
translate Korean lorem1_1097c581:

    # Lo "Yes, but you are so different from other mammals we know that, ultimately, you are quite unique. We don't know any other sentient mammals."
    Lo "그래요, 하지만 우리가 알고 있는 포유류와는 너무나도 달라요. 매우 독특하죠. 우리는 지각이 있는 포유류에 대해 몰라요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:564
translate Korean lorem1_adad4e4d:

    # c "You've got a point there, I'll give you that."
    c "일리가 있네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:566
translate Korean lorem1_6dae6f38:

    # c "Strangely enough, we have plenty of human-like creatures in our mythologies as well."
    c "이상하게, 우리의 신화에도 인간과 같은 생명체가 등장해요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:568
translate Korean lorem1_3a0f9dbc:

    # Lo happy "Oh, do tell!"
    Lo happy "아, 정말요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:570
translate Korean lorem1_84b644db:

    # c "You already mentioned ghosts, but some other ones include dwarves, giants, faeries and blemmyes."
    c "언급하신 귀신도 있고, 드워프라던지, 거인들이라던지, 요정이나 블레미도 있죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:572
translate Korean lorem1_99cc5a9c:

    # Lo normal "I think I've heard of most of these before, but what is a blemmyes?"
    Lo normal "대부분은 들어본 것 같네요. 근데 블레미는 뭐에요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:574
translate Korean lorem1_bc61390c:

    # c "Essentially, a blemmyes is a human without a head."
    c "기본적으로, 블레미는 머리가 없는 인간이에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:576
translate Korean lorem1_13a0d3a7:

    # Lo think "A human without a head? How does that work? How do they eat?"
    Lo think "머리가 없는 인간이요? 그게 가능해요? 음식을 어떻게 먹어요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:578
translate Korean lorem1_23045a97:

    # c "Instead of a head, they just have all their facial features on their chest."
    c "머리는 없지만, 얼굴이 가슴 부분에 달려있죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:580
translate Korean lorem1_c56b9fcb:

    # Lo relieved "That's a rather weird mental image."
    Lo relieved "실제로 보면 이상하겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:582
translate Korean lorem1_6ab78f6e:

    # c "There are also a lot of half-creatures that share some characteristics with humans and other animals."
    c "인간과 동물의 특징이 있는 수많은 종류의 반인반수도 있고요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:584
translate Korean lorem1_abec4e3c:

    # Lo think "Like merhumans?"
    Lo think "인어처럼요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:586
translate Korean lorem1_c48dc32f:

    # c "Sure."
    c "그렇죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:588
translate Korean lorem1_3aea1e4e:

    # c "Lastly, there are creatures that are said to be able to shapeshift into human form."
    c "마지막으로, 인간의 모습으로 변할 수 있다는 생물들도 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:590
translate Korean lorem1_e783f80f:

    # c "Strangely enough, some of our dragon myths said they could shapeshift into humans or that certain countries’ royalty are descended from dragons."
    c "게다가, 용들에 관한 신화 중에서는 용이 인간의 모습으로 변할 수 있어 몇몇 국가의 왕족들은 용의 후손이라고도 하고 있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:592
translate Korean lorem1_3ff38ba7:

    # Lo normal "That would imply that they are genetically compatible with humans."
    Lo normal "유전적으로 인간과 용이 서로 일치할 수 있겠군요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:612
translate Korean lorem1_abdd03bc:

    # Lo think "Sounds rather outlandish, if you ask me. We certainly can't shapeshift like that."
    Lo think "그렇게 들으니 이상하네요. 우리는 확실히 변신할 수 없는데."

# game/lorem1.rpy:621
translate Korean lorem1_6b37c29e:

    # Lo normal "Right. To be fair, we do have a lot of myths that seem quite out there as well compared to what you're like."
    Lo normal "확실해요. 저희도 대사님이 말씀하신 것들이랑 비슷한 신화들이 많아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:627
translate Korean lorem1_2752c6e4:

    # Lo happy "To be fair, I never tried. Hang on."
    Lo happy "솔직히, 시도도 해보지 않았아요. 잠시만요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:629
translate Korean lorem1_8ee9d226:

    # Lo think "..."
    Lo think "..."

# game/lorem1.rpy:631
translate Korean lorem1_a28401a3:

    # Lo normal "Did it work?"
    Lo normal "됐어요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:633
translate Korean lorem1_020d6ce0:

    # c "Nope, still a dragon."
    c "아뇨, 아직도 용이시네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:635
translate Korean lorem1_6a9873c0:

    # Lo sad "Awww."
    Lo sad "히잉."

# game/lorem1.rpy:638
translate Korean lorem1_ec4292d5:

    # Lo think "Anyway, how come you know so much about myths?"
    Lo think "아무튼, 어떻게 신화를 그렇게 많이 아세요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:640
translate Korean lorem1_2a92c8b3:

    # c "All part of being an ambassador. Not only did I learn about dragon myths in order to compare them to what you're like, but I also studied myths about creatures that are similar to humans so I could find out how similar they were to yours."
    c "제가 대사기 때문이죠. 실제로 당신들이 어떻게 생겼을 지 비교하려고 용에 대한 신화를 배웠을 뿐만 아니라, 당신들의 신화와 얼마나 비슷한지 비교하려고 인간들의 신화를 배우기도 했죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:642
translate Korean lorem1_0b33fa04:

    # Lo happy "Well, you're doing an excellent job so far. And it's bound to help me a lot with my game as well."
    Lo happy "음, 지금까지 잘 해주신 것 같네요. 제 게임에 많은 도움이 될 것 같고요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:644
translate Korean lorem1_9d229f6a:

    # c "You're going to put all of that into the game?"
    c "제가 말씀드린 걸 모두 게임에 넣으실 생각이에요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:646
translate Korean lorem1_23818b09:

    # Lo normal "Let's just say it gives me some excellent material to work with."
    Lo normal "제가 작업할 수 있도록 훌륭한 재료가 되었다고 말씀드려두죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:648
translate Korean lorem1_433c0d98:

    # c "I thought you wanted to give an accurate portrayal of humans, not just collect myths."
    c "전 그냥 단지 신화를 수집하는 정도로 끝날게 아니라 인간을 정확하게 묘사하고 싶으신 걸로 알고 있었는데요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:650
translate Korean lorem1_baea8985:

    # Lo think "One species will certainly be modeled after you, but that doesn't mean we can't introduce some variety with the others."
    Lo think "종 하나는 확실히 대사님을 모델삼아 만들겠지만, 다른 종들을 넣지 않아서 다양하게 만들지 않겠다는 건 아니니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:652
translate Korean lorem1_610f35b2:

    # Lo happy "People will love it if we also bring some of the more unusual myths to life."
    Lo happy "사람들은 특이한 신화들을 일상 속으로 가져온 것도 좋아해줄 거에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:654
translate Korean lorem1_89aefe22:

    # c "I see."
    c "알았어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:656
translate Korean lorem1_415eea89:

    # Lo normal "But since we also want each of the normal human characters to be unique, I'd like to know how much variety there really is within your species."
    Lo normal "하지만 정상적인 인간들끼리도 서로 얼마나 차이가 있는 지 알고 싶어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:658
translate Korean lorem1_bea9746d:

    # Lo think "I've seen Reza before, so comparing him to you already gives me a bit of an idea - but how far do these differences go, exactly?"
    Lo think "레자 님을 봤는데, 대사님과 비교해보니까 차이가 있다는 건 알겠더라고요. 그런데 정확히 어디까지 차이가 날 수 있는 거에요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:660
translate Korean lorem1_14145a58:

    # Lo "When we arrived here, you asked me if I was old enough to drink. That leads me to believe that your average human must be a lot taller."
    Lo "대사님이 여기 도착하셨을 때, 술을 마셔도 되는 나이인지 물어보셨잖아요. 그렇게 말씀하시니까 그 때 보통의 인간은 훨씬 크겠거니 생각했죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:662
translate Korean lorem1_fa74b8ac:

    # c "That's true. You could say Reza would be about average for an adult."
    c "맞아요. 레자 정도면 보편적인 성인이라고 볼 수 있죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:664
translate Korean lorem1_375c6cbb:

    # c "Not that it would be impossible to get a good deal bigger than him or even smaller than you, but those cases are rather rare and usually the result of medical conditions."
    c "당신보다 작은 사람도 있고 레자보다 큰 사람도 가끔 있지만, 보통은 환경에 따라 달라요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:666
translate Korean lorem1_285740c1:

    # Lo normal "I see, I see."
    Lo normal "알았어요, 알았어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:668
translate Korean lorem1_2447aed2:

    # Lo "What about colors? Are there any humans who are blue like me?"
    Lo "색은요? 저처럼 푸른 색인 인간도 있나요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:670
translate Korean lorem1_f72e6b17:

    # c "Not really. There is a certain spectrum of skin colors that can be lighter or darker, but so far I've seen a lot more variety in the dragons here."
    c "아니요. 사람에 따라 피부색이 저보다 밝거나 어두울 수는 있지만, 지금까지 봤을 때 용족의 피부색이 더 다양한 것 같네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:672
translate Korean lorem1_602f23e2:

    # c "We do have quite a number of different eye colors, though."
    c "다만 홍채의 색깔이 꽤 다양하죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:674
translate Korean lorem1_6a49ecc6:

    # Lo think "Interesting."
    Lo think "흥미롭군요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:676
translate Korean lorem1_ae0c3ac6:

    # c "As for things that aren't immediately visible, we also have different blood types, but I assume you know about that."
    c "물론 눈으로 보이진 않긴 하지만, 우리는 혈액형도 달라요. 하지만 그건 당신도 알 것 같네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:678
translate Korean lorem1_7f71981e:

    # Lo normal "We certainly have those as well."
    Lo normal "우리도 마찬가지로 달라요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:680
translate Korean lorem1_43482f04:

    # c "Some people even believe your blood type influences your personality."
    c "몇몇 사람들은 혈액형에 따라 성격이 다르다고까지 믿고 있죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:682
translate Korean lorem1_fc46b979:

    # Lo think "That, on the other hand, is news to me."
    Lo think "어, 그건, 저한테는 처음 듣는 얘긴데요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:684
translate Korean lorem1_61e5afcb:

    # c "Anything else you want to know?"
    c "다른 알고 싶으신 거라도 있으세요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:686
translate Korean lorem1_845133b1:

    # Lo relieved "Phew, we already got so much. I'll have to think about if and how we can work all this into the game."
    Lo relieved "휴, 이미 많은 걸 얻은 것 같아요. 이 모든 걸 게임에 넣을 수 있을 방법을 고민해봐야겠어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:688
translate Korean lorem1_b184e63b:

    # c "Have you worked on any other games before?"
    c "혹시 다른 게임도 제작해보셨나요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:690
translate Korean lorem1_de842598:

    # Lo normal "I worked on a few small projects during the course of my studies and also interned at a studio before. This is on a completely different level, though."
    Lo normal "학업 중에 몇몇 작은 프로젝트나 스튜디오에서 인턴으로 일해본 적은 있어요. 하지만, 이건 완전히 다른 레벨의 문제네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:692
translate Korean lorem1_be8b7287_1:

    # c "How so?"
    c "그래요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:694
translate Korean lorem1_e26e90cd:

    # Lo happy "It's my game, so I'm the one calling the shots here. It's a very different thing than just making a few graphics when you're part of a bigger team, for sure."
    Lo happy "이건 저만 만드는 게임이잖아요. 훨씬 더 큰 팀에 있었을 때 그래픽 몇 개를 만드는 것과는 차원이 다르죠, 확실히."

# game/lorem1.rpy:696
translate Korean lorem1_86819a05:

    # c "I see. How long exactly have you been working on this?"
    c "그렇군요. 얼마나 걸릴 것 같아요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:698
translate Korean lorem1_7a1ab47b:

    # Lo think "Phew. Must be several months now. I've got everything planned out and a lot of the groundwork has already been done."
    Lo think "휴. 지금은 몇 달 정도 되겠네요. 전 이미 모든 걸 계획해뒀고, 이미 기본은 다들 짜여져있어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:700
translate Korean lorem1_b055803d:

    # Lo normal "The most difficult things are the characters themselves, and to make sure all of the details are accurate."
    Lo normal "가장 어려운 건 아무래도 캐릭터겠네요. 세세한 것들 하나하나 정확하게 만들어야하니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:702
translate Korean lorem1_4e8c7062:

    # c "Of course."
    c "물론이죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:704
translate Korean lorem1_a51215b8:

    # c "Have you shown the game to other people yet?"
    c "다른 사람들에게 보여준 적 있어요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:706
translate Korean lorem1_a371ebeb:

    # Lo happy "Sure! Feedback is a very important part of the development process, so I regularly gather ideas and opinions from others. I even made a website to do this!"
    Lo happy "물론이죠! 개발 과정에 있어서 피드백은 가장 중요한 거니까요. 다른 사람들로부터 아이디어나 의견을 수집하기도 좋고요. 웹사이트까지 만들어뒀어요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:708
translate Korean lorem1_d21af984:

    # c "And what do they say?"
    c "사람들이 뭐라고 해요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:710
translate Korean lorem1_835230ec:

    # Lo think "All kinds of things, really. Sometimes it's hard to decide which ones have a good point and which can be disregarded."
    Lo think "말 그대로 모든 것들을 말해줘요. 가끔은 어떤 게 좋은지 어떤 걸 넣지 말아야할지 결정하기 어려워요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:712
translate Korean lorem1_2afa4c62:

    # Lo normal "Overall, it seems there are many people who are looking forward to play my game, though."
    Lo normal "하지만 크게 보자면 제 게임을 기대하고 있는 사람들이 많다는 것이겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:714
translate Korean lorem1_d9d4691f:

    # c "How many are we talking about?"
    c "얼마나 많다는 건데요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:716
translate Korean lorem1_5c0f4648:

    # Lo "I don't know, exactly. The counter on my website only tracks the number of visits, so I don’t actually know how many different people there are."
    Lo "정확히는 몰라요. 웹사이트에선 조회수만 집계해서, 얼마나 많은 다른 사람들이 있는지는 잘 모르겠어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:718
translate Korean lorem1_9b25687c:

    # c "What if it doesn't work out?"
    c "잘 안 되면 어떻게 하죠?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:720
translate Korean lorem1_346b54b1:

    # Lo think "What do you mean?"
    Lo think "그게 무슨 말씀이세요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:722
translate Korean lorem1_efc51e51:

    # c "Well, you're investing a certain amount of time and money into making this game. Ideally, you would make back your investment and hopefully get some profit on top of that."
    c "음, 당신은 게임 제작에 꽤 큰 돈과 시간을 투자하고 있잖아요. 이상적으로는, 당신은 당신의 투자만큼 돌려받을 것이고 그 이상으로 어떤 이익을 얻겠죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:724
translate Korean lorem1_869998d9:

    # Lo normal "If the goal is to make money, sure. However, I just wanted to try my hand at doing something like this. If some people are going to enjoy the end result, that's great."
    Lo normal "물론, 목표가 돈을 버는 건 맞아요. 하지만, 저는 그냥 제 손으로 직접 이런 일을 해보고자 했어요. 사람들이 조금이라도 즐겼다면, 그걸로 충분해요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:726
translate Korean lorem1_1ed5e1ae:

    # Lo happy "Don't forget that I'll also have made something that I can put on my resume. At the very least, it'll have been a good learning experience."
    Lo happy "게다가 이력서에 넣을 만한 것도 만들어낼거니까요. 적어도, 이건 제게 좋은 경험이 될 거에요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:728
translate Korean lorem1_ab1f35dd:

    # c "With that attitude, I suppose you really don't have anything to lose."
    c "그런 마음가짐이면, 잃으실 건 없겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:730
translate Korean lorem1_1c92ddc7:

    # Lo think "I can always look for another job, and maybe I'll end up working at a game studio, but I think once I've started doing something like that, I might not get this opportunity again."
    Lo think "다른 직업을 찾을 기회는 많고, 어쩌면 게임 스튜디오에서 일하게 될 지도 모르지만, 아무튼 일단 일을 시작하게 되면 이런 기회를 다시 얻을 수 있을 것 같지 않아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:732
translate Korean lorem1_aa53918d:

    # c "So it's now or never, huh?"
    c "그래서, 지금이 아니면 안된다는 말씀이시죠?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:734
translate Korean lorem1_9f523b59:

    # Lo normal "In a nutshell, yes."
    Lo normal "정리하자면 그렇죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:736
translate Korean lorem1_99384fb3:

    # c "And that all works out with your courier job?"
    c "그런데 택배 일과 같이 할 수 있겠어요?"

# game/lorem1.rpy:738
translate Korean lorem1_11dcf77f:

    # Lo happy "Sure. I can support myself this way and am not really under any pressure, since I don't have any deadlines to keep."
    Lo happy "물론이죠. 일을 해야 제가 계속 작업할 수 있기도 하고, 성급해야할 필요도 없어요. 마감 기한 같은 게 없으니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:745
translate Korean lorem1_823bd1ea:

    # Lo "I'd like to think so!"
    Lo "저도 그렇게 생각해요!"

# game/lorem1.rpy:753
translate Korean lorem1_ebb6432d:

    # Lo think "You're right about that. It's something where balance is important, I think. I set deadlines for myself, but I don't have to worry about the project breaking down if I don't meet certain milestones at a certain time."
    Lo think "그건 맞는 말씀이네요. 어딜가든 밸런스가 중요하니까요. 저 스스로 기한을 정해두긴 했지만, 어느 날에 어느 부분까지 진행되지 않았다고 해서 프로젝트가 무산될 염려는 없어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:756
translate Korean lorem1_8455dd24:

    # c "What kind of tools are you using to make it? If I consider what some of your species look like, I'm having a hard time imagining how the bigger ones could program a game."
    c "어떻게 만드실 생각이에요? 당신처럼 용족들의 모습을 생각해보면, 덩치가 큰 사람들은 프로그래밍하기 꽤나 어려울 것 같은데요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:758
translate Korean lorem1_16ced629:

    # Lo normal "While we do have devices tailored to each individual species, I can't deny that my dextrous hands make it a lot easier compared to some of the others."
    Lo normal "각각 체형에 맞는 장치를 가지고 있긴 하지만, 확실히 작업하는 데에 있어서 제 손이 다른 사람들보다 적합하긴 해요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:760
translate Korean lorem1_f7462fd2:

    # Lo "One downside is that I have to keep my nails short, or else using the keyboard gets a bit cumbersome."
    Lo "단점이 있다면 손톱을 짧게 해야 키보드를 사용하는 데 번거롭지 않다는 것이죠."

# game/lorem1.rpy:762
translate Korean lorem1_df4298d3:

    # c "I imagine you'd have to be careful with those while working as a courier, anyway."
    c "그러면 배달원으로 일하실 때도 조심하셔야겠네요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:764
translate Korean lorem1_088e6966:

    # Lo relieved "You're right about that. One wrong move and you've suddenly shredded the letter you were just going to hand to someone."
    Lo relieved "대사님이 맞아요. 한 번이라도 잘못 건드렸다간 누군가에게 전해져야 할 편지가 찢어지니까요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:779
translate Korean lorem1_9041e3cd:

    # Lo normal "Luckily, that kind of thing doesn't really happen to me anymore."
    Lo normal "다행히도, 그런 사고는 더 이상 일어나지 않았어요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:781
translate Korean lorem1_b7ad971f:

    # Lo "Not only because of the shorter nails, but once you've worked there for a while, you just learn to be more careful."
    Lo "짧은 손톱 때문이 아니더라도, 거기서 일하다보면 조심하는 방법을 배우게 되는 것 같아요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:783
translate Korean lorem1_57968227:

    # Lo think "It's a bit sad not to have them as a natural letter opener anymore, though."
    Lo think "그렇지만 편지 봉투를 열어주는 도구 같은 게 없다는 게 좀 안타까워요."

# game/lorem1.rpy:785
